WARNING!!! these instructions have not been completed, don't complain if they don't work for you
================================================================================================

Build instructions:

Mac OSX (latest tested 10.6)
Make sure you have the Developer Tools installed, you can get them from Apple http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/xcode/id448457090?mt=12

1 - Set up Git and configure GitHub [http://help.github.com/mac-set-up-git/]

2 - Clone the repository: 
	- Open the terminal and execute the following commands:
	- Go to the folder where you want the prototype folder to be created
		cd /path/to/directory
	- Clone the repo:
		git clone git://github.com/AXR/Prototype.git
		
3 - Download and install all required libraries:
	- Boost:
		http://sourceforge.net/projects/boost/files/boost/1.49.0/boost_1_49_0.zip/download

    	- Expat:
		http://sourceforge.net/projects/expat/files/latest/download?_test=goal
		
	- Cairo:
		Dependencies:
			- Pixman: http://cairographics.org/releases/pixman-0.22.2.tar.gz
		Library:
			- Cairo: http://www.cairographics.org/releases/cairo-1.10.2.tar.gz
			
	- Pango:
		Dependencies:
			- GLib: ftp://ftp.gnome.org/pub/gnome/sources/glib/2.29/glib-2.29.6.tar.bz2
			- Libiconv: http://ftpmirror.gnu.org/libiconv/libiconv-1.14.tar.gz
		Library:
			- Pango: http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/pango/1.28/pango-1.28.4.tar.bz2

4 - Open the Xcode project (prototype/mac/AXR Test App.xcodeproj) and hit Run



Windows: coming soon...